This paper deals with the computational complexity of membrane systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves investigating the connectivity properties of dependency graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the characterisation of complexity classes such as L and NL, which are topics in computational complexity theory (cs.LO). The paper also involves investigating acceptance conditions for membrane systems, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves proving correctness of the results obtained, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.SC).
